window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>She's the one woman I'd give anything to forget - and now, I'm stuck living with her.</b></p> <p>I'm making a fresh start in Lake Tahoe, until my stubborn sister decides to move Mira into our cabin. I'll be damned if I move out on Mira's account.</p> <p>Nothing has changed in the years since I last saw Mira. Her tempting body and smart mouth taunt me daily. The only hope I have at keeping my sanity is the knowledge that Mira is hiding something.</p> <p>Sooner or later, I'll discover her secret, and knowing her, it'll be damning. But first, I have to ignore the urge to kiss and touch and make Mira mine again.</p> <p><b>Excerpt:</b></p> <p>I grab her waist, guiding her back against the shelves.</p> <p>She kisses my cheekbone, nibbles my earlobe. \"We can't do this here.\"</p> <p>That nibble shoots straight to my groin. \"I beg to differ. I think we can manage.\"</p> <p><b>Once the walls come down, emotions run hot. Grab&nbsp;</b><b><i>Never Date Your Ex</i></b><b>, a humorous, steamy, second-chance romance!</b>&nbsp;</p> <p><b>Previously titled </b><b><i>Rebound Roommate</i></b><b>.</b></p>"; 
